prtFrStatisTable.description: This table is applicable only for an active port running an FR protocol .

prtFrStatisSltIdx.name: prtFrStatisSltIdx
prtFrStatisSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid. For stand-alone units this index will be notApplicable (255).

prtFrStatisPrtIdx.name: prtFrStatisPrtIdx
prtFrStatisPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number.

prtFrStatisInvIdx.name: prtFrStatisInvIdx
prtFrStatisInvIdx.description: The Interval of 15 min. for which the following statistics counters are applicable.

prtFrTimeElapsed.name: prtFrTimeElapsed
prtFrTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current error-measurement interval. This object is applicable mainly for the current interval. For other interval: - if data is available: value will be 899. - if data is not available: value will be 0.

prtFrRxTotalFrames.name: prtFrRxTotalFrames
prtFrRxTotalFrames.description: The total number of frames received by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrTxTotalFrames.name: prtFrTxTotalFrames
prtFrTxTotalFrames.description: The total number of frames sent by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrRxTotalBytes.name: prtFrRxTotalBytes
prtFrRxTotalBytes.description: The total number of bytes received by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrTxTotalBytes.name: prtFrTxTotalBytes
prtFrTxTotalBytes.description: The total number of bytes sent by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrRxMngFrames.name: prtFrRxMngFrames
prtFrRxMngFrames.description: The management number of frames received by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrTxMngFrames.name: prtFrTxMngFrames
prtFrTxMngFrames.description: The management number of frames sent by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrRxDeFrames.name: prtFrRxDeFrames
prtFrRxDeFrames.description: The number of De frames received by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrTxDeFrames.name: prtFrTxDeFrames
prtFrTxDeFrames.description: The number of De frames sent by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrRxDcrdCongDeFr.name: prtFrRxDcrdCongDeFr
prtFrRxDcrdCongDeFr.description: The number of De frames discarded due to congestion, received by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrTxDcrdCongDeFr.name: prtFrTxDcrdCongDeFr
prtFrTxDcrdCongDeFr.description: The number of De frames discarded due to congestion, sent by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrRxDcrdCongAllFr.name: prtFrRxDcrdCongAllFr
prtFrRxDcrdCongAllFr.description: All the frames discarded due to congestion, received by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrTxDcrdCongAllFr.name: prtFrTxDcrdCongAllFr
prtFrTxDcrdCongAllFr.description: All the frames discarded due to congestion, sent by this port during the selected interval.

prtFrRxFecn.name: prtFrRxFecn
prtFrRxFecn.description: Number of frames received by this port during the selected interval, indicating forward congestion.

prtFrTxFecn.name: prtFrTxFecn
prtFrTxFecn.description: Number of frames sent by this port during the selected interval, indicating forward congestion.

prtFrRxBecn.name: prtFrRxBecn
prtFrRxBecn.description: Number of frames received by this port during the selected interval, indicating backward congestion.

prtFrTxBecn.name: prtFrTxBecn
prtFrTxBecn.description: Number of frames sent by this port during the selected interval, indicating backward congestion.

prtFrRxBeViol.name: prtFrRxBeViol
prtFrRxBeViol.description: Number of data frames received by this port during the selected interval, exceeding the Burst Excess value.

prtFrTxBeViol.name: prtFrTxBeViol
prtFrTxBeViol.description: Number of data frames sent by this port during the selected interval, exceeding the Burst Excess value.

prtFrRxBcViol.name: prtFrRxBcViol
prtFrRxBcViol.description: Number of data frames received by this port during the selected interval, exceeding the Burst Committed value.

prtFrTxBcViol.name: prtFrTxBcViol
prtFrTxBcViol.description: Number of data frames sent by this port during the selected interval, exceeding the Burst Committed value.

prtCrStatisTable.name: prtCrStatisTable
prtCrStatisTable.description: This table is applicable only for an active port running a CR protocol .

prtCrStatisSltIdx.name: prtCrStatisSltIdx
prtCrStatisSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid. For stand-alone units this index will be notApplicable (255).

prtCrStatisPrtIdx.name: prtCrStatisPrtIdx
prtCrStatisPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number.

prtCrStatisInvIdx.name: prtCrStatisInvIdx
prtCrStatisInvIdx.description: The Interval of 15 min. for which the following statistics counters are applicable.

prtCrTimeElapsed.name: prtCrTimeElapsed
prtCrTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current error-measurement interval. This object is applicable mainly for the current interval. For other interval: - if data is available: value will be 899. - if data is not available: value will be 0.

prtCrRxTotalCells.name: prtCrRxTotalCells
prtCrRxTotalCells.description: The total number of cells received by this port during the selected interval.

prtCrTxTotalCells.name: prtCrTxTotalCells
prtCrTxTotalCells.description: The total number of cells sent by this port during the selected interval.

prtCrRxDataCells.name: prtCrRxDataCells
prtCrRxDataCells.description: The number of Data Cells received by this port during the selected interval.

prtCrTxDataCells.name: prtCrTxDataCells
prtCrTxDataCells.description: The number of Data Cells sent by this port during the selected interval.

prtDlciStatisTable.name: prtDlciStatisTable
prtDlciStatisTable.description: This table is applicable only for an active port running an FR, FR+ or CR protocol, with valid DLCIs .

prtDlciSltIdx.name: prtDlciSltIdx
prtDlciSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid. For stand-alone units this index will be notApplicable (255).

prtDlciPrtIdx.name: prtDlciPrtIdx
prtDlciPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number.

prtDlciIdx.name: prtDlciIdx
prtDlciIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique DLCI index for each valid DLCI (16..991).

prtDlciRxDeFrames.name: prtDlciRxDeFrames
prtDlciRxDeFrames.description: The number of De frames received by this DLCI.

prtDlciTxDeFrames.name: prtDlciTxDeFrames
prtDlciTxDeFrames.description: The number of De frames sent by this DLCI.

prtDlciRxDcrdCongDeFr.name: prtDlciRxDcrdCongDeFr
prtDlciRxDcrdCongDeFr.description: The number of De frames discarded due to congestion, received by this DLCI.

prtDlciTxDcrdCongDeFr.name: prtDlciTxDcrdCongDeFr
prtDlciTxDcrdCongDeFr.description: The number of De frames discarded due to congestion, sent by this DLCI.

prtDlciRxDcrdCongAllFr.name: prtDlciRxDcrdCongAllFr
prtDlciRxDcrdCongAllFr.description: All the frames discarded due to congestion, received by this DLCI.

prtDlciTxDcrdCongAllFr.name: prtDlciTxDcrdCongAllFr
prtDlciTxDcrdCongAllFr.description: All the frames discarded due to congestion, sent by this DLCI.

prtDlciTxFecn.name: prtDlciTxFecn
prtDlciTxFecn.description: Number of frames sent by this DLCI, indicating forward congestion.

prtDlciTxBecn.name: prtDlciTxBecn
prtDlciTxBecn.description: Number of frames sent by this DLCI, indicating backward congestion.

prtDlciRxBeViol.name: prtDlciRxBeViol
prtDlciRxBeViol.description: Number of data frames received by this DLCI, exceeding the Burst Excess value.

prtDlciTxBeViol.name: prtDlciTxBeViol
prtDlciTxBeViol.description: Number of data frames sent by this DLCI, exceeding the Burst Excess value.

prtDlciRxBcViol.name: prtDlciRxBcViol
prtDlciRxBcViol.description: Number of data frames received by this DLCI, exceeding the Burst Committed value.

prtDlciTxBcViol.name: prtDlciTxBcViol
prtDlciTxBcViol.description: Number of data frames sent by this DLCI, exceeding the Burst Committed value.

prtT1FdlMsgTable.name: prtT1FdlMsgTable
prtT1FdlMsgTable.description: This table is applicable for a T1 interface with 'esf' LineType .

prtT1FdlMsgSltIdx.name: prtT1FdlMsgSltIdx
prtT1FdlMsgSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid.

prtT1FdlMsgPrtIdx.name: prtT1FdlMsgPrtIdx
prtT1FdlMsgPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. MTML-1/T1 modules have just one external interface.

prtT1FdlMsgFdlTxRx.name: prtT1FdlMsgFdlTxRx
prtT1FdlMsgFdlTxRx.description: The Fdl tx/rx reference of the Fdl message.

prtExTsSplitTable.name: prtExTsSplitTable
prtExTsSplitTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtExTsCnfgIdx.name: prtExTsCnfgIdx
prtExTsCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtExTsSltIdx.name: prtExTsSltIdx
prtExTsSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid. notApplicable - for stand-alone units.

prtExTsPrtIdx.name: prtExTsPrtIdx
prtExTsPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. Most ML cards have only one external interface. inPrt1 - for MTML-H/E1 cards. For other products' index see their specification.

prtExTsIdx.name: prtExTsIdx
prtExTsIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique time slot position. The valid time slots are: 1..24 for T1 Card and 1..31 for E1 interface. In G732S-E1 lines, time slot 16 is not valid for data, it is dedicated to multiframe synchronization bits and voice signaling.

prtExTsBit.name: prtExTsBit
prtExTsBit.description: This attribute indicates a unique Bit within the time slot. The valid Bits are: 1..8.

prtExTsIConSlot.name: prtExTsIConSlot
prtExTsIConSlot.description: This attribute indicates whether the specified time slot is connected/routed internally in the Agent and to which card it is connected. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid. notApplicable - for stand-alone units.

prtExTsIConPrt.name: prtExTsIConPrt
prtExTsIConPrt.description: This attribute indicates the internally (In Mux) connected/routed port. For other products' index see their specification.

prtAgendaBehaviourTable.name: prtAgendaBehaviourTable
prtAgendaBehaviourTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtAgendaBehaviourCnfgIdx.name: prtAgendaBehaviourCnfgIdx
prtAgendaBehaviourCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtAgendaBehaviourSltIdx.name: prtAgendaBehaviourSltIdx
prtAgendaBehaviourSltIdx.description: This parameter should be: - slot number for MX3000 - 255 = N/A for MX300/30.

prtAgendaBehaviourPrtIdx.name: prtAgendaBehaviourPrtIdx
prtAgendaBehaviourPrtIdx.description: This parameter should be: - port number for MX300/30 - 100 = N/A for MX3000.

prtAgendaBehaviourOnOff.name: prtAgendaBehaviourOnOff
prtAgendaBehaviourOnOff.description: Setting this command to on(3) enables the agenda function at module (3000) or port (300/30) level.

prtCnfgAgendaTable.name: prtCnfgAgendaTable
prtCnfgAgendaTable.description: This table allows the user to schedule the time a session is active per week basis.

prtCnfgAgendaCnfgIdx.name: prtCnfgAgendaCnfgIdx
prtCnfgAgendaCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtCnfgAgendaSltIdx.name: prtCnfgAgendaSltIdx
prtCnfgAgendaSltIdx.description: This attribute is equal to: -slot number for MX3000 -255 = N/A for MX300/30

prtCnfgAgendaPrtIdx.name: prtCnfgAgendaPrtIdx
prtCnfgAgendaPrtIdx.description: This attribute is equal to: -port number for MX300/30 -100 = N/A for MX3000

prtCnfgAgendaDayIdx.name: prtCnfgAgendaDayIdx
prtCnfgAgendaDayIdx.description: This attribute for which day of the week this row applies.

prtCnfgAgendaSesId.name: prtCnfgAgendaSesId
prtCnfgAgendaSesId.description: The user may define 4 different active intervals per day.

prtCnfgAgendaFrom.name: prtCnfgAgendaFrom
prtCnfgAgendaFrom.description: Start from time interval in seconds.

prtGenCnfgTable.name: prtGenCnfgTable
prtGenCnfgTable.description: This table allows the user to configure general port parameters.

prtGenCnfgIdx.name: prtGenCnfgIdx
prtGenCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg. The write operation is valid only to the TmpCnfg.

prtGenCnfgSltIdx.name: prtGenCnfgSltIdx
prtGenCnfgSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted.

prtGenCnfgPrtIdx.name: prtGenCnfgPrtIdx
prtGenCnfgPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique external or internal port number. For MP: exPrt1 (1) .. exPrt12 (12) , notApplicable(100), inPrt1 (101) .. inPrt48 (148)

prtGenCnfgLinkToSlot.name: prtGenCnfgLinkToSlot
prtGenCnfgLinkToSlot.description: This attribute indicates the slot of the ML card to which the IO port is mapped.

prtGenCnfgLinkToPort.name: prtGenCnfgLinkToPort
prtGenCnfgLinkToPort.description: This attribute indicates the port in the prtGenCnfgLinkToSlot of the ML card to which the IO port is mapped. For MP: exPrt1 (1) , exPrt2 (2) , exPrt3 (3) , exPrt4 (4) , inPrt1 (101) notApplicable (255)

prtGenCnfgPortId.name: prtGenCnfgPortId
prtGenCnfgPortId.description: IO Port Id for V5.1 use. This object is applicable only for part of the PSTN and ISDN IO ports. Generally, 0 is a valid value. Nevertheless, for ports that do not support this object, the value will be: notApplicable= 0

prtCmprTypIdx.name: prtCmprTypIdx
prtCmprTypIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Type of the Compressed being referred.

prtCmprCnfgIdx.name: prtCmprCnfgIdx
prtCmprCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the configuration to which the Compressed information is related.

prtCmprVersion.name: prtCmprVersion
prtCmprVersion.description: This attribute indicates the version of the internal format of the Compressed data

prtCmprSltIdx.name: prtCmprSltIdx
prtCmprSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique number of the slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries psB(2),clB(4),io6(10)..io(16) are not valid.

prtCmprPrtIdx.name: prtCmprPrtIdx
prtCmprPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique identifier of the port the compressed information relates to. Valid values: exPrt1 (1) .. exPrt12 (12) , inPrt1 (101) .. inPrt48 (148).

prtCmprObj.name: prtCmprObj
prtCmprObj.description: This attribute is the compressed information itself.

prtDlciCmprCnfgIdx.name: prtDlciCmprCnfgIdx
prtDlciCmprCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the configuration to which the Compressed information is related.

prtDlciCmprVersion.name: prtDlciCmprVersion
prtDlciCmprVersion.description: This attribute indicates the version of the internal format of the Compressed data

prtDlciCmprSltIdx.name: prtDlciCmprSltIdx
prtDlciCmprSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique number of the slot position where the module is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries psB(2),clB(4),io6(10)..io(16) are not valid.

prtDlciCmprPrtIdx.name: prtDlciCmprPrtIdx
prtDlciCmprPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique identifier of the port the compressed information relates to. All the values are valid.

prtDlciCmprDlciIdx.name: prtDlciCmprDlciIdx
prtDlciCmprDlciIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique identifier of the Dlci the compressed information relates to. The values are between 16 - 991.

prtDlciCmprObj.name: prtDlciCmprObj
prtDlciCmprObj.description: This attribute is the compressed information itself.

prtAlarmsCmprVersion.name: prtAlarmsCmprVersion
prtAlarmsCmprVersion.description: This attribute indicates the version of the internal format of the Compressed data

prtAlarmsCmprAlarmSlot.name: prtAlarmsCmprAlarmSlot
prtAlarmsCmprAlarmSlot.description: This attribute indicates the desired slot position. In the ?004 Unit the entries PsB(2),ClB(4),io6(10)..io(16) are not valid. For Stand-alone units, notApplicable(255) will appear.

prtAlarmsCmprAlarmPort.name: prtAlarmsCmprAlarmPort
prtAlarmsCmprAlarmPort.description: This attribute indicates a unique identifier of the port the alarm applies to. All the values are valid. No alarms exist for a non-physical port

prtAlarmsCmprAlarmIdx.name: prtAlarmsCmprAlarmIdx
prtAlarmsCmprAlarmIdx.description: A unique number to identify an entry in the alarm status table of the agent.

prtAlarmsCmprObj.name: prtAlarmsCmprObj
prtAlarmsCmprObj.description: This attribute is the compressed information itself.

prtSExHsfSltIdx.name: prtSExHsfSltIdx
prtSExHsfSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid.

prtSExHsfPrtIdx.name: prtSExHsfPrtIdx
prtSExHsfPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number.

prtSExHsfInterfaceTyp.name: prtSExHsfInterfaceTyp
prtSExHsfInterfaceTyp.description: This attribute indicates a unique interface type of a selected port.

prtSExHsfRts.name: prtSExHsfRts
prtSExHsfRts.description: This attribute indicates a unique RTS control signal state.

mdlPbxFramerCnfgTable.name: mdlPbxFramerCnfgTable
mdlPbxFramerCnfgTable.description: This table contains parameters relevant to a module belonging to a digital voice system, except mdlPbxFraEnhEcho which is relevant also for analog cards.

mdlPbxFraCnfgIdx.name: mdlPbxFraCnfgIdx
mdlPbxFraCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

mdlPbxFraSltIdx.name: mdlPbxFraSltIdx
mdlPbxFraSltIdx.description: The slot relevant to this module.

mdlPbxFraEnhEcho.name: mdlPbxFraEnhEcho
mdlPbxFraEnhEcho.description: Refers to external ports of an analogue module and to the internal ports of the other mvc4 types of modules. ms16(3) means that the four voice ports have enhanced echo of 16ms. ms32(4) means that the two first ports have enhanced echo of 32 ms while the last two ports have no enhanced echo.

mdlPbxFraTSGroupAss.name: mdlPbxFraTSGroupAss
mdlPbxFraTSGroupAss.description: In case of T1 modules: group1=(1,2,3,4), ...., group6=(21,22,23,24) while in case of E1 modules: - If prtExPh1MlLineType=g732sE1 or g732sE1CRC: group1=(1,2,3,4),..,group4=(13,14,15,17), group5=(18,19,20,21),...,group7=(26,27,28,29) group8=(30,31). - If prtExPh1MlLineType=g732nE1 or g732nE1CRC: group1=(1,2,3,4),..,group4=(13,14,15,16), group5=(17,18,19,20),...,group7=(25,26,27,28) group8=(29,30,31).

mdlPbxFraSignalMode.name: mdlPbxFraSignalMode
mdlPbxFraSignalMode.description: Refers to the signaling mode of the Framer module. tieTrunk(2), tieInvert(3), casTrans(4) are standard coding of the signaling protocol. casTrans(4) is Channel Associated Signaling (the signaling is within the channels time slot). ccsTrans(6) is Common Channel Signaling (the signaling is not within the channels time slot). userDefined(5) allows the user to define the signaling protocol he wants. In this case, the next two MIB fields are relevant.

mdlPbxFraSignalVector.name: mdlPbxFraSignalVector
mdlPbxFraSignalVector.description: In the case of mdlPbxFraSignalMode = userDefined(5), this field defines the A,B,C Bits. D bit is supplied for future versions. Bit 1 = Bit A ON Hook - Local Bit 2 = Bit B ON Hook - Local Bit 3 = Bit C ON Hook - Local Bit 4 = Bit D ON Hook - Local Bit 5 = Bit A OFF Hook - Local Bit 6 = Bit B OFF Hook - Local Bit 7 = Bit C OFF Hook - Local Bit 8 = Bit D OFF Hook - Local Bit 9 = Bit A ON Hook - Remote Bit 10 = Bit B ON Hook - Remote Bit 11 = Bit C ON Hook - Remote Bit 12 = Bit D ON Hook - Remote Bit 13 = Bit A OFF Hook - Remote Bit 14 = Bit B OFF Hook - Remote Bit 15 = Bit C OFF Hook - Remote Bit 16 = Bit D OFF Hook - Remote In conjunction with the Mask, mdlPbxFraSignalMask, it is possible to compute the signal mode.

mdlPbxFraSignalMask.name: mdlPbxFraSignalMask
mdlPbxFraSignalMask.description: In the case of mdlPbxFraSignalMode = userDefined(5), this field defines the 'don't care' A,B,C Bits. D bit is supplied for future versions. Bit 1 = Bit A ON Hook - Local Bit 2 = Bit B ON Hook - Local Bit 3 = Bit C ON Hook - Local Bit 4 = Bit D ON Hook - Local Bit 5 = Bit A OFF Hook - Local Bit 6 = Bit B OFF Hook - Local Bit 7 = Bit C OFF Hook - Local Bit 8 = Bit D OFF Hook - Local Bit 9 = Bit A ON Hook - Remote Bit 10 = Bit B ON Hook - Remote Bit 11 = Bit C ON Hook - Remote Bit 12 = Bit D ON Hook - Remote Bit 13 = Bit A OFF Hook - Remote Bit 14 = Bit B OFF Hook - Remote Bit 15 = Bit C OFF Hook - Remote Bit 16 = Bit D OFF Hook - Remote.

mdlPbxFraFramerSlot.name: mdlPbxFraFramerSlot
mdlPbxFraFramerSlot.description: Slot where is sitting the Framer.

mdlPbxFraSignaling.name: mdlPbxFraSignaling
mdlPbxFraSignaling.description: Signaling - describes the way the signaling ABCD bits pass from the local extension to the remote extension and vice-versa. endToEnd = the signaling ABCD bits pass without change from local to remote extension. localTermination = the signaling ABCD bits received from the local extension are translated to different ON Hook/OFF Hook bit values and then passed to remote extension. This is relevant when the Local and Remote ON Hook/OFF Hook values are different.

prtExClCnfgEntry.name: prtExClCnfgEntry
prtExClCnfgEntry.description: All the entries at this table are identical (have the same value) for all the configurations (1..100) except the TmpCnfg. The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtExClCnfgIdx.name: prtExClCnfgIdx
prtExClCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtExClSltIdx.name: prtExClSltIdx
prtExClSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. Because the second Cl is only for redundancy, all the parameters are identical in the two modules, i.e. change of any parameter in one module will change automatically the value of the other module.. In the ?004 Unit the entry clB(4) is not valid.

prtExClPrtIdx.name: prtExClPrtIdx
prtExClPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number.

prtExClUsage.name: prtExClUsage
prtExClUsage.description: This attribute indicates what is the usage of the port.

prtExClRate.name: prtExClRate
prtExClRate.description: This attribute indicates the operation rate of the port.

prtExClDataBits.name: prtExClDataBits
prtExClDataBits.description: This attribute indicates the number of data bits in async frame

prtExClParity.name: prtExClParity
prtExClParity.description: This attribute indicates if the parity operation mode in async frame

prtExClStopBits.name: prtExClStopBits
prtExClStopBits.description: This attribute indicates the minimum number of stop bits in the tx async frame

prtExClRoutingProtocol.name: prtExClRoutingProtocol
prtExClRoutingProtocol.description: This attribute indicates the routing protocol of the port. When prtExClUsage is nmsSlip or nmsPpp - all values are applicable . Else - only 'none' is applicable.

prtExPh1MlCnfgTable.name: prtExPh1MlCnfgTable
prtExPh1MlCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtExPh1MlCnfgIdx.name: prtExPh1MlCnfgIdx
prtExPh1MlCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtExPh1MlSltIdx.name: prtExPh1MlSltIdx
prtExPh1MlSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid.

prtExPh1MlPrtIdx.name: prtExPh1MlPrtIdx
prtExPh1MlPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. MTML-1/E1 and MTML-1/T1 cards have only one external interface. inPrt1 - for MTML-H/E1 cards. exPrt2..exPrt4 - for MTML-4 cards and others.

prtExPh1MlConnect.name: prtExPh1MlConnect
prtExPh1MlConnect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms. It also affects all the card considerations because it may indicate that the module has only one physical interface.

prtExPh1MlLineType.name: prtExPh1MlLineType
prtExPh1MlLineType.description: This attribute is the line type parameter for T1/E1 interface. The user should select only the parameters which are relevant to the specific card: T1 line code parameters for the MPH.1/T1 E1 line code parameters for the MPH.1/E1. This parameter has the same values as dsx1LineType in T1/E1 MIB (RFC-1406). The parameters in dsx1LineType are: other (1) esfT1 dsx1ESF (2) sfT1 dsx1D4 (3) g732nE1 dsx1E1 (4) g732nE1CRC dsx1E1-CRC (5) g732sE1 dsx1E1-MF (6) g732sE1CRC dsx1E1-MF-CRC (7)

prtExPh1MlLineCode.name: prtExPh1MlLineCode
prtExPh1MlLineCode.description: This attribute is the line code parameter used for T1/E1 interface. The user should select only the parameters which are relevant to the specific card: T1 line code parameters for MPH.1/T1 E1 line code parameters for MPH.1/E1. This parameter has the same values as dsx1LineCoding in T1/E1 MIB (RFC-1406). The parameters in dsx1LineCoding are: dsx1JBZS (1) dsx1B8ZS (2) dsx1HDB3 (3) dsx1ZBTSI (4) dsx1AMI (5) other (6)

prtExPh1MlLineLen.name: prtExPh1MlLineLen
prtExPh1MlLineLen.description: This attribute is the line length parameter used only for T1/DSU interfaces. lenXXXpXXXft = len-XXX-XXXft.

prtExPh1MlRestoreTime.name: prtExPh1MlRestoreTime
prtExPh1MlRestoreTime.description: The time passing from the disappearance of the loss of synchronization condition (red alarm) to the restoration of normal service. The options 1secFast(2) and 10sec62411(3) for E1 interfaces are proprietary implementation of the T1 standard to the E1 interface.

prtExPh1MlTxGain.name: prtExPh1MlTxGain
prtExPh1MlTxGain.description: This attribute is the tx gain parameter used only for T1/CSU interfaces.

prtExPh1MlRxSensitivity.name: prtExPh1MlRxSensitivity
prtExPh1MlRxSensitivity.description: This attribute is the rx line sensitivity parameter. low26dBm, high36dBm - applicable for T1-CSU shortHaul, longHaul - applicable for MTML-4 cards.

prtExPh1MlIdleCode.name: prtExPh1MlIdleCode
prtExPh1MlIdleCode.description: Determines the code for transmission in empty time slots. Type value(00-FFH), Excluding 0H,8H,10H,12H,21H,24H,42H,49H, 84H,92H

prtExPh1MlTdmTrunk.name: prtExPh1MlTdmTrunk
prtExPh1MlTdmTrunk.description: This attribute indicates whether the port is used to transfer TDM cards data and through which Bus.

prtExPh1MlClkMode.name: prtExPh1MlClkMode
prtExPh1MlClkMode.description: Defines the clock operation mode of the T1/E1 interface. Ports that are connected to the TDM Buses must be in nodalTiming(3) clock mode.

prtExPh1MlMfClkSrcSlt.name: prtExPh1MlMfClkSrcSlt
prtExPh1MlMfClkSrcSlt.description: This attribute indicates whether the port Tx multiframe is synchronized with Rx multiframe of another port and the slot position of that port. This operation is required in order to bypass signaling of PCM voice channels. Its value is always local(2) when the port isn't connected to any TDM bus. When it's value is local(2) there is no meaning to 'prtExPh1MlMfClkSrcPrt' parameter. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid

prtExPh1MlMfClkSrcPrt.name: prtExPh1MlMfClkSrcPrt
prtExPh1MlMfClkSrcPrt.description: A unique number to identify a port position in the mux. It has no effect when the prtExPh1MlMfClkSrcSlt selected is Local. inPrt1 - for MTML-H/E1 cards.

prtExPh1MlFdlType.name: prtExPh1MlFdlType
prtExPh1MlFdlType.description: A unique number to identify the side of the FDL operation. Normal: 'response' for the user side and 'command' for the PTT side. Applicable only when working with ESF-T1 link

prtExPh1MlInbandMng.name: prtExPh1MlInbandMng
prtExPh1MlInbandMng.description: A unique number to identify an Inband management over the link.

prtExPh1MlInbandMngRate.name: prtExPh1MlInbandMngRate
prtExPh1MlInbandMngRate.description: A unique number to identify the rate of the Inband management. E1 port - it is not applicable when prtExPh1MlInbandMng selected is off. T1 port - it is not applicable when prtExPh1MlInbandMng selected is off OR fdlOrTs0.

prtExPh1MlRedundType.name: prtExPh1MlRedundType
prtExPh1MlRedundType.description: This object determines the ML redundancy type: none - no ML redundacy dualCableAIS - each ML card is connected by a separate dualCableParallelTx cable to the other MUX (two cables connect two MUXes). There are two types of dual redundancy. yCable - Y cable is connected to both ML cards (one cable connects two MUXes). Default=none When only one ML card exists, the type can be only 'none'. The value should be the same for both ML slots.

prtExPh1MlRedundSlot.name: prtExPh1MlRedundSlot
prtExPh1MlRedundSlot.description: This object indicates the slot containing the redundacy ML card, coupled with the current ML (prtExPh1MlSltIdx). When prtExPh1MlRedundType=none (no ML redundancy) this object will be 'notApplicable'. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid When value is not 'none', it should be mutual to the redundant ML slot.

prtExPh1MlRedundPort.name: prtExPh1MlRedundPort
prtExPh1MlRedundPort.description: This object indicates the redundacy ML port, coupled with the current ML port (prtExPh1MlPrtIdx). When prtExPh1MlRedundType=none (no ML redundancy) this object will be 'notApplicable'. When value is not 'none', it should be mutual to the redundant ML port. inPrt1 - for MTML-H/E1 cards. exPrt2..exPrt4 - for MTML-4 cards.

prtExPh1MlRedundRecTime.name: prtExPh1MlRedundRecTime
prtExPh1MlRedundRecTime.description: Redundancy Recovery Time (sec). After switching the ML card to the current (prtExPh1MlSltIdx), the next ML switch can be performed only after a minimum time, indicated by this object.

prtExPh1MlInbandMngRoutProt.name: prtExPh1MlInbandMngRoutProt
prtExPh1MlInbandMngRoutProt.description: This attribute indicates the Inband Mng routing protocol of the port.

prtExPh1MlIfType.name: prtExPh1MlIfType
prtExPh1MlIfType.description: Interface type of the port. For T1 - csu, dsu are the valid values For E1 - dsu, ltu are the valid values.

prtExPh1MlTsTable.name: prtExPh1MlTsTable
prtExPh1MlTsTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtExPh1MlTsCnfgIdx.name: prtExPh1MlTsCnfgIdx
prtExPh1MlTsCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtExPh1MlTsSltIdx.name: prtExPh1MlTsSltIdx
prtExPh1MlTsSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid

prtExPh1MlTsPrtIdx.name: prtExPh1MlTsPrtIdx
prtExPh1MlTsPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. MPH.1/E1 and MPH.1/T1 cards have only one external interface. exPrt2 - for ME1-2, MT1-2 and mhsPri cards. exPrt3, exPrt4 - for mhsPri cards. inPrt1 - for MTML-H/E1 cards.

prtExPh1MlTsIdx.name: prtExPh1MlTsIdx
prtExPh1MlTsIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique time slot position. The valid time slots are 1..24 for T1 Card and 1..31 for E1 interface. In G732S-E1 lines time slot 16 is not valid for data, it is dedicated for multiframe synchronization bits and voice signaling.

prtExPh1MlTsIConSlot.name: prtExPh1MlTsIConSlot
prtExPh1MlTsIConSlot.description: This attribute indicates whether the specified time slot is connected/routed internally in the Agent and to which card it is connected. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid. split - will be used when the Src TS is connected to more than one slot OR more than one port (each needing less than a whole TS).

prtExPh1MlTsIConPrt.name: prtExPh1MlTsIConPrt
prtExPh1MlTsIConPrt.description: This attribute indicates the internally (In Mux) connected/routed port. For MP, the values will be: { exPrt1 (1) , exPrt2 (2) , exPrt3 (3) , exPrt4 (4) , exPrt5 (5) , exPrt6 (6) , exPrt7 (7) , exPrt8 (8) , exPrt9 (9) , exPrt10 (10) , exPrt11 (11) , exPrt12 (12) , noConnect (100), inPrt1 (101) , inPrt2 (102) , inPrt3 (103) , inPrt4 (104) , inPrt5 (105) , inPrt6 (106) , inPrt7 (107) , inPrt8 (108) , inPrt9 (109) , inPrt10 (110) , inPrt11 (111) , inPrt12 (112) }

prtExPh1MlTsIConTs.name: prtExPh1MlTsIConTs
prtExPh1MlTsIConTs.description: This attribute indicates a unique time slot position. The valid time slots are 1..24 for T1 Card and 1..31 for E1 interface. In G732S-E1 lines time slot 16 is not valid for data, it is dedicated to multiframe synchronization and voice signaling.

prtExPh1MlTsExt.name: prtExPh1MlTsExt
prtExPh1MlTsExt.description: A pointer to an extension of this table: prtExTsSplitTable. - If prtExPh1MlTsIConSlot='split', its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER of the prtExTsSplitTable, with its relevant CnfgIdx, SltIdx, PrtIdx, TsIdx and 1st TsBit. - If prtExPh1MlTsIConSlot is not 'split', its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

prtInPh1MlCnfgTable.name: prtInPh1MlCnfgTable
prtInPh1MlCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtInPh1MlCnfgIdx.name: prtInPh1MlCnfgIdx
prtInPh1MlCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtInPh1MlSltType.name: prtInPh1MlSltType
prtInPh1MlSltType.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. For ISDN BRI port of MX300/30: io1(5) = isdn1(5) and io2(6) = isdn2(6) In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid

prtInPh1MlPrtIdx.name: prtInPh1MlPrtIdx
prtInPh1MlPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. MPH.1/E1 and MPH.1/T1 cards have three internal interfaces. MX3000 modules may have up to 50 internal ports.

prtInPh1MlConnect.name: prtInPh1MlConnect
prtInPh1MlConnect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms.

prtInPh1MlRate.name: prtInPh1MlRate
prtInPh1MlRate.description: This attribute indicates the port speed.

prtInPh1MlProtocol.name: prtInPh1MlProtocol
prtInPh1MlProtocol.description: This attribute indicates the applied protocol.

prtInPh1MlConnectionTyp.name: prtInPh1MlConnectionTyp
prtInPh1MlConnectionTyp.description: This attribute indicates the link connection type. It is required for three reasons: FR/CR Inband management operation (LMI,CLMM...). CIR check. NMS network management. SameNetManaged - indicates network internal line. SameNetNotMana - indicates network internal line, but the remote mux is not managed by the nms. User - User to Network Interface. OtherNet - Network To Network Interfce. PubNet - Access Mux To PubNet Interface.

prtInPh1MlCongResponse.name: prtInPh1MlCongResponse
prtInPh1MlCongResponse.description: This attribute indicates how to handle the congestion indication to/from the mux internal connection side (for example transmit/receive becn to/from the network). no - do nothing FlowControl - translate the congestion indication between the port and the internal connection port according to the definition of the prtInPh1MlFlowControl parameters. The operation is done in both directions.

prtInPh1MlCongLevel.name: prtInPh1MlCongLevel
prtInPh1MlCongLevel.description: This attribute indicates the level of delayed data in precents of the total available dynamic memory, for which the port will start to operate . The resolution of the parameter is 5 percent. Valid values: 10..70, 255. 255=notApplicable.

prtInPh1MlTc.name: prtInPh1MlTc
prtInPh1MlTc.description: This attribute indicates the Tc parameter which is the time period of the sliding window in which the Bc/Be are tested. The value of this parameter is identical for all the ports in the specific card. 255=notApplicable.

prtInPh1MlFlowControl.name: prtInPh1MlFlowControl
prtInPh1MlFlowControl.description: This attribute indicates the required flow control betweeen the port and the remote equipment.

prtInPh1MlSegment.name: prtInPh1MlSegment
prtInPh1MlSegment.description: This object is the Segmentation in Bytes. In protocol FR+, ISDN internals, MX 30/300 the segmentation is: 50 (2) ,158 (3) ,266 (4) ,376 (5), 484 (6) In MX 3000/4: For protocol FR+ (internal ISDN ports of MHS.S, MHS.U, MHS.E1, MHS.T1 cards) segmentation values are: 236 (7),472 (8), 708 (9), 944 (10) ,1180 (11)

prtInPh1MlFrMngProt.name: prtInPh1MlFrMngProt
prtInPh1MlFrMngProt.description: This object indicates the Frame-Relay management protocol. ansiT1 = ANSI T1.617 Annex D (this is the default value). This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols. When prtInPh1MlConnectionTyp = sameNetManaged, this object will be RO (internally determined).

prtInPh1MlEnqPeriod.name: prtInPh1MlEnqPeriod
prtInPh1MlEnqPeriod.description: This object is the Status Enquiry Period, in seconds. It determines the frequency of the Status Enquiry message as sent by the FR user side. At the FR network side, it determines the timeout for this message reception. Default = 4 seconds. This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtInPh1MlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none). 0=notApplicable.

prtInPh1MlFullRptPeriod.name: prtInPh1MlFullRptPeriod
prtInPh1MlFullRptPeriod.description: This object is the Full Report Frequency. It determines the number of the Status Enquiry messages sent by the FR user side, before a Full Report Request is sent. The units are : Status Enquiry messages (periods). Valid values: 1 .. 255. 255 = infinite (never sent). This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtInPh1MlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none). 0=notApplicable.

prtInPh1MlFrWindowSize.name: prtInPh1MlFrWindowSize
prtInPh1MlFrWindowSize.description: This object is the FR Window Size. It determines the number of samplings in the sliding window that counts the errors. This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtInPh1MlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none). 0=notApplicable.

prtInPh1MlErrorsThreshold.name: prtInPh1MlErrorsThreshold
prtInPh1MlErrorsThreshold.description: This object is the Max Errors. It determines the number of Status Enquiry Errors that occured within the FR sliding window, before this port is considered DOWN (threshold). This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtInPh1MlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none). 0=notApplicable.

prtInPh1MlMaxIdleTime.name: prtInPh1MlMaxIdleTime
prtInPh1MlMaxIdleTime.description: Move to higher prioritized connected link after this period of seconds of silence on the current link. 0=Never. Never move to higher prioritized connected link. UNIT is seconds. Valid values are: 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 120, 180, 240, 300, 360, 420, 480, 540, 600, 900, 1200, 1500, 1800. Attempt to Set an invalid value will result in getting the default value.

prtInPh1MlBearerCh.name: prtInPh1MlBearerCh
prtInPh1MlBearerCh.description: Defines which B (bearer) channels are used for transferring ISDN data. Default value is: none (255). anyChannel (2) is skipped because it is not in use here.

prtInPh1MlAssociatedExCh.name: prtInPh1MlAssociatedExCh
prtInPh1MlAssociatedExCh.description: This object indicates the external port associated to this internal port. At present, it is used by the Hybrid (mp2100h), MHS-4 cards which can have up to 64 dynamic internal ports associated with External ports. For ISDN cards, the value will be: notApplicable (255). The associated external of an ISDN internal port is represented by the MIB object: prtIsdnDirectoryPrtNu.

prtInPh1MlClockEncoding.name: prtInPh1MlClockEncoding
prtInPh1MlClockEncoding.description: This object is the Encoding type of the Line. This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols.

prtInPh1MlMinSeparators.name: prtInPh1MlMinSeparators
prtInPh1MlMinSeparators.description: Minimum number of bytes separating between two adjacent frames (HDLC item). 0 = notApplicable

prtInPh1MlCcittCrc.name: prtInPh1MlCcittCrc
prtInPh1MlCcittCrc.description: This object indicates how many Bits are used for CRC (HDLC item).

prtInPh1MlFrameSeparator.name: prtInPh1MlFrameSeparator
prtInPh1MlFrameSeparator.description: This object indicates what should be transferred on the line when there are no frames to pass (HDLC item). idles: mean that FF will pass on the line flags: mean that 7E will pass on the line.

prtInPh1MlDlciTable.name: prtInPh1MlDlciTable
prtInPh1MlDlciTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtInPh1MlDlciCnfgIdx.name: prtInPh1MlDlciCnfgIdx
prtInPh1MlDlciCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtInPh1MlDlciSltIdx.name: prtInPh1MlDlciSltIdx
prtInPh1MlDlciSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid

prtInPh1MlDlciPrtIdx.name: prtInPh1MlDlciPrtIdx
prtInPh1MlDlciPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique internal port number. MPH.1/E1 and MPH.1/T1 cards have three internal ports.

prtInPh1MlDlciIdx.name: prtInPh1MlDlciIdx
prtInPh1MlDlciIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique index for each possible used dlci(16..991). When the protocol is not Multiplexing protocol, then its type is 'user' and the only valid index is 1.

prtInPh1MlDlciValid.name: prtInPh1MlDlciValid
prtInPh1MlDlciValid.description: This attribute indicates whether the attributes in this entry are valid or not. The user can add/delete pvc (dlci to dlci connection) by modifing this object

prtInPh1MlDlciIConSlt.name: prtInPh1MlDlciIConSlt
prtInPh1MlDlciIConSlt.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position In the Mux (Agent) where the dlci is routed to. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid

prtInPh1MlDlciIConPrt.name: prtInPh1MlDlciIConPrt
prtInPh1MlDlciIConPrt.description: This attribute indicates a unique port id which the dlci is routed to.

prtInPh1MlDlciIConDlci.name: prtInPh1MlDlciIConDlci
prtInPh1MlDlciIConDlci.description: This attribute indicates a unique internal connection dlci number which the src dlci is routed to.

prtInPh1MlDlciTxBc.name: prtInPh1MlDlciTxBc
prtInPh1MlDlciTxBc.description: This attribute indicates a unique Tx committed bandwidth on the user transmit line or at the port receive line.

prtInPh1MlDlciTxBe.name: prtInPh1MlDlciTxBe
prtInPh1MlDlciTxBe.description: This attribute indicates a unique Tx excess bandwidth on the user transmit line or at the port receive line.

prtInPh1MlDlciRxBc.name: prtInPh1MlDlciRxBc
prtInPh1MlDlciRxBc.description: This attribute indicates a unique Rx committed bandwidth on the user receive line or at the port transmit line.

prtInPh1MlDlciRxBe.name: prtInPh1MlDlciRxBe
prtInPh1MlDlciRxBe.description: This attribute indicates a unique Rx excess bandwidth on the user receive line or at the port transmit line.

prtInPh1MlDlciPriority.name: prtInPh1MlDlciPriority
prtInPh1MlDlciPriority.description: This attribute indicates a unique priority of the pcv. 1 is the lowest priority and 8 is the highest priority.

prtInPh1MlDlciStatus.name: prtInPh1MlDlciStatus
prtInPh1MlDlciStatus.description: This attribute indicates the status of the pvc. The status is disconnected(1) when one of the sides is programmed as not connected

prtPhMlCnfgTable.name: prtPhMlCnfgTable
prtPhMlCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtPhMlCnfgIdx.name: prtPhMlCnfgIdx
prtPhMlCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtPhMlSltIdx.name: prtPhMlSltIdx
prtPhMlSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the module is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid.

prtPhMlPrtIdx.name: prtPhMlPrtIdx
prtPhMlPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. ML-20 cards have just one external interface.

prtPhMlConnect.name: prtPhMlConnect
prtPhMlConnect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms.

prtPhMlRate.name: prtPhMlRate
prtPhMlRate.description: This attribute indicates the port speed.

prtPhMlCAS.name: prtPhMlCAS
prtPhMlCAS.description: This attribute indicates whether Channel Associated Signaling (CAS) is used.

prtPhMlSyncRestore.name: prtPhMlSyncRestore
prtPhMlSyncRestore.description: Sync Restoration time, in seconds. notApplicable=0.

prtPhMlBus.name: prtPhMlBus
prtPhMlBus.description: The TDM BUS this port is linked to.

prtPhMlMfSyncSlot.name: prtPhMlMfSyncSlot
prtPhMlMfSyncSlot.description: This attribute indicates whether the sync is synchronized according to a certain card and the slot of this card. This operation is required in order to bypass signaling of PCM voice channels. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid

prtLogicalCnfgTable.name: prtLogicalCnfgTable
prtLogicalCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtLogicalCnfgIdx.name: prtLogicalCnfgIdx
prtLogicalCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtLogicalSltIdx.name: prtLogicalSltIdx
prtLogicalSltIdx.description: Slot Index. For ISDN BRI Ports of MX300/30, io1(5) = isdn1(5) and io2(6) = isdn2(6).

prtLogicalPrtIdx.name: prtLogicalPrtIdx
prtLogicalPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. This port number should be an internal port number: inPrt1(101)->inPrt50(150), linkSel1(200)->linkSel50(250), encaps1(300)-> encaps50(350), huntGr1(101) -> huntGr10(110).

prtLogicalConnect.name: prtLogicalConnect
prtLogicalConnect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms.

prtLogicalFunction.name: prtLogicalFunction
prtLogicalFunction.description: This parameter defines the function of the relevant channel.

prtLogicalRowStatus.name: prtLogicalRowStatus
prtLogicalRowStatus.description: This parameter allows the NMS to create/delete logical ports.

linkSelectorCnfgTable.name: linkSelectorCnfgTable
linkSelectorCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

linkSelectorCnfgIdx.name: linkSelectorCnfgIdx
linkSelectorCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

linkSelectorPrtIdx.name: linkSelectorPrtIdx
linkSelectorPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. This port number should be internal port number: higher or equal to linkSeL1(201).

linkSelectorMaxIdleTime.name: linkSelectorMaxIdleTime
linkSelectorMaxIdleTime.description: Move to higher prioritized connected link after this period of seconds of silence on the current link. 0=move immediately to higher prioritized connected link. UNIT is seconds.

linkSelectorMode.name: linkSelectorMode
linkSelectorMode.description: If the link selector is in mode: backup(2)=then the link with the lower priority will be used in case of failure of the higher priority link, bod(3)=bandwidth on demand or dynamic bandwidth allocation means that links with lower priority will be used whenever additional bandwidth is required.

linkSelectorRevert.name: linkSelectorRevert
linkSelectorRevert.description: If the link selector is in mode backup: auto(2)=return automatically to Main link when it is OK. manual(3)=stays connected to backup link.

linkSelectorMinBUSession.name: linkSelectorMinBUSession
linkSelectorMinBUSession.description: Minimum duration of a backup session before returning to Main Link. Relevant in Backup Mode and when Revert is auto(2). Value 255 is for NEVER which means never return to Main Link. UNIT is minutes.

linkSelectorPLinkTable.name: linkSelectorPLinkTable
linkSelectorPLinkTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

pLinkCnfgIdx.name: pLinkCnfgIdx
pLinkCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

pLinkPrtIdx.name: pLinkPrtIdx
pLinkPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. This port number should be the link selector number.

pLinkIdx.name: pLinkIdx
pLinkIdx.description: This index is the row number.

pLinkSlotNu.name: pLinkSlotNu
pLinkSlotNu.description: The slot of the prioritized link. For ISDN BRI ports of MX300/30, io1(5) = isdn1(5) and io2(6) = isdn2(6).

pLinkPortNu.name: pLinkPortNu
pLinkPortNu.description: The port of the prioritized link. Value 100 is for noConnect.

pLinkPrioNu.name: pLinkPrioNu
pLinkPrioNu.description: The priority of the prioritized link. MIN=1...., MAX=8.

pLinkVRate.name: pLinkVRate
pLinkVRate.description: The rate to use with this link.

prtExPhPlCnfgTable.name: prtExPhPlCnfgTable
prtExPhPlCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtExPhPlCnfgIdx.name: prtExPhPlCnfgIdx
prtExPhPlCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtExPhPlSltIdx.name: prtExPhPlSltIdx
prtExPhPlSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid

prtExPhPlPrtIdx.name: prtExPhPlPrtIdx
prtExPhPlPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. In case of PH.1 card, only exPrt(1) is valid.

prtExPhPlConnect.name: prtExPhPlConnect
prtExPhPlConnect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms.

prtExPhPlHRate.name: prtExPhPlHRate
prtExPhPlHRate.description: This attribute indicates the port speed for HIGH speed cards. The card has limitations about the maximum sigma channel speeds and about the possible rates for each clock mode . N - The rate is valid for DCE and EXT-DCE Nodal clock mode. L - The rate is valid for DCE and EXT-DCE Local clock mode. E - The rate is valid for DTE External clock mode. 'r9d6KbpsNLE' means rate of 9.6 Kbps ('d'=dot). Note: Some rate attributes have been changed. As the MIB was already released with the old attributes, the names of the options were not changed. The new names + attributes are in a comment. Example: r2048KbpsE (63), -- r2048KbpsNLE

prtExPhPlLRate.name: prtExPhPlLRate
prtExPhPlLRate.description: This attribute indicates the port speed for LOW speed cards. The card has limitations about the possible rates for each clock mode. N - The rate is valid for DCE and EXT-DCE Nodal clock mode. L - The rate is valid for DCE and EXT-DCE Local clock mode. E - The rate is valid for DTE External clock mode. Note: Some rate attributes have been changed. As the MIB was already released with the old attributes, the names of the options were not changed. The new names + attributes are in a comment. Example: r57600bpsLE (16), -- r57600bpsNLE

prtExPhPlProtocol.name: prtExPhPlProtocol
prtExPhPlProtocol.description: This object indicates the applied protocol.

prtExPhPlConnectionTyp.name: prtExPhPlConnectionTyp
prtExPhPlConnectionTyp.description: This attribute indicates the link connection type. It is required for three reasons: FR/CR Inband management opration (LMI,CLMM...). CIR check. NMS network management. SameNetManaged - indicates network internal line. SameNetMotMana - indicates network internal line, but the remote mux is not managed by the NMS. User - User to Network Interface. OtherNet - Network To Network Interface. PubNet - Access Mux To PubNet Interface.

prtExPhPlDceClkSrc.name: prtExPhPlDceClkSrc
prtExPhPlDceClkSrc.description: This attribute indicates the source of the clock when working in dce or ext-dce clock mode. notApplicable(1) - is applied for dte(3) and lbt(5) clock modes. When clock mode is dte, the clock source is always external, therefore this object's value is notApplicable. local(2) and nodalTiming(3) - are valid in dce(1), extDce(2) or int(4) clock modes. The recommended clock source is local(2).

prtExPhPlCongResponse.name: prtExPhPlCongResponse
prtExPhPlCongResponse.description: This attribute indicates how to handle the congestion indication to/from the mux internal connection side (for example transmit/received becn to/from the network). no - do nothing flowControl - translates the congestion indication between the port and the internal connection port according to the definition of the prtInPh1MlFlowControl parameters. The operation is done on both directions. toFlowControl- translates the backward congestion indication received from the internal connection port (normally the network side) to flow control and do nothing in the other direction.

prtExPhPlCongLevel.name: prtExPhPlCongLevel
prtExPhPlCongLevel.description: This attribute indicates the level of delayed data in precents of total available dynamic memory, for which the port will start to operate as congested. The resolution of the parameter is 5 percent.

prtExPhPlTc.name: prtExPhPlTc
prtExPhPlTc.description: This attribute indicates the Tc parameter which is the time period of the sliding window in which the Bc/Be are tested. The value of this parameter is identical for all the ports of a specific card .

prtExPhPlFlowControl.name: prtExPhPlFlowControl
prtExPhPlFlowControl.description: This attribute indicates the required flow control betweeen the port and the remote equipment. fecnBecn - is valid only for FR, FR+ and CR protocols. xonXoff,dtrCts - are valid only for Async protocols. speedReduction - is valid only for DLC protocol when the Clock Mode is DCE and the Clock Source is Local.

prtExPhPlDcdRts.name: prtExPhPlDcdRts
prtExPhPlDcdRts.description: Protocol may require end to end connect indication over the network. End to end link connection establishment over the FR network will be indicated to the user by using DCD or RTS control signals, depending on the clock mode: DCE or DTE respectively. The options are : - On : DCD(DCE)/RTS(DTE) will be constantly ON no matter if the End to End connection is established or not. - End to End: The DCD(DCE)/RTS(DTE) will be according to the status of the End to End connection.

prtExPhPlDcdRtsControlPath.name: prtExPhPlDcdRtsControlPath
prtExPhPlDcdRtsControlPath.description: Protocol may require end to end connect indication over the network. This parameter defines whether to take the user connection status (RTS(DCE)/DCD(DTE)) and forward it to the network side. - on : Transmit active connection to the network regardless the RTS/DCD control lines status. - off: Transmit active connection to the network according to the status of the RTS/DCD pin.

prtExPhPlDataBits.name: prtExPhPlDataBits
prtExPhPlDataBits.description: This attribute indicates the number of data bits in async frame. It is relevant only for Async protocols.

prtExPhPlParity.name: prtExPhPlParity
prtExPhPlParity.description: This attribute indicates the parity operation mode in async frame. It is relevant only for Async protocols.

prtExPhPlStopBits.name: prtExPhPlStopBits
prtExPhPlStopBits.description: This attribute indicates the minimum number of stop bits in the tx async frame. It is relevant only for Async protocols.

prtExPhPlLXon.name: prtExPhPlLXon
prtExPhPlLXon.description: This attribute indicates the character used as X-On to notify receive enable. This parameter is valid only for async protocols. Valid values: 0..255. The value 256 indicates that it's not applicable

prtExPhPlLXoff.name: prtExPhPlLXoff
prtExPhPlLXoff.description: This attribute indicates the character used as X-Off to notify receive disable. This parameter is valid only for async protocols. Valid values: 0..255. The value 256 indicates that it's not applicable

prtExPhPlFrMngProt.name: prtExPhPlFrMngProt
prtExPhPlFrMngProt.description: This object indicates the Frame-Relay management protocol. ansiT1 = ANSI T1.617 Annex D (this is the default value). This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols. When prtExPhPlConnectionTyp = sameNetManaged, this object will be RO (internally determined).

prtExPhPlEnqPeriod.name: prtExPhPlEnqPeriod
prtExPhPlEnqPeriod.description: This object is the Status Enquiry Period, in seconds. It determines the frequency of the Status Enquiry message as sent by the FR user side. At the FR network side, it determines the timeout for this message reception. Default = 4 seconds. This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtExPhPlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none).

prtExPhPlFullRptPeriod.name: prtExPhPlFullRptPeriod
prtExPhPlFullRptPeriod.description: This object is the Full Report Frequency. It determines the number of the Status Enquiry messages sent by the FR user side, before a Full Report Request is sent. The units are : Status Enquiry messages (periods). Valid values: 1 .. 255. 255 = infinite. This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtExPhPlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none).

prtExPhPlFrWindowSize.name: prtExPhPlFrWindowSize
prtExPhPlFrWindowSize.description: This object is the FR Window Size. It determines the number of samplings in the sliding window that counts the errors. This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtExPhPlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none).

prtExPhPlErrorsThreshold.name: prtExPhPlErrorsThreshold
prtExPhPlErrorsThreshold.description: This object is the Max Errors. It determines the number of Status Enquiry Errors that occured within the FR sliding window, before this port is considered DOWN (threshold). This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtExPhPlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none).

prtExPhPlPvcCreateMsg.name: prtExPhPlPvcCreateMsg
prtExPhPlPvcCreateMsg.description: This object is Update Message (if required or not). It determines whether a message of a New PVC Creation is requested or not (yes/no). Default = no. This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtExPhPlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none).

prtExPhPlCllmMsg.name: prtExPhPlCllmMsg
prtExPhPlCllmMsg.description: This object is CLLM Message (if required or not). It determines whether to send (or not) a congestion message when the port is Rx congested. Default = no. This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols AND only when prtExPhPlFrMngProt is NOT (notApplicable or none).

prtExPhPlProtDelayLevel.name: prtExPhPlProtDelayLevel
prtExPhPlProtDelayLevel.description: This object is the Segmentation in Bytes. In some cases, the enumerated values will mean other segmentation values than specified: Product: MX-3000 MX-3000 MX-300/MX-30 Protocol: FR+ Transparent FR+ ----------------------------------------------------- level 1 50 Bytes 44 Bytes 50 Bytes level 2 158 Bytes 155 Bytes 158 Bytes level 3 266 Bytes 266 Bytes 266 Bytes level 4 376 Bytes 377 Bytes 376 Bytes level 5 484 Bytes 488 Bytes 484 Bytes Defval=level 1 value This parameter is applicable only for FR+ and transparent protocols.

prtExPhPlClockEncoding.name: prtExPhPlClockEncoding
prtExPhPlClockEncoding.description: This object is the Encoding type of the Line. This parameter is applicable only for FR and FR+ protocols.

prtExPhPlMinSeparators.name: prtExPhPlMinSeparators
prtExPhPlMinSeparators.description: Minimum number of bytes separating between two adjacent frames (HDLC item). 0 = notApplicable

prtExPhPlCcittCrc.name: prtExPhPlCcittCrc
prtExPhPlCcittCrc.description: This object indicates how many Bits are used for CRC (HDLC item).

prtExPhPlFrameSeparator.name: prtExPhPlFrameSeparator
prtExPhPlFrameSeparator.description: This object indicates what should be transferred on the line when there are no frames to pass (HDLC item). idles: mean that FF will pass on the line flags: mean that 7E will pass on the line.

prtExPhPlDlciTable.name: prtExPhPlDlciTable
prtExPhPlDlciTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only at the TmpCnfg entry.

prtExPhPlDlciCnfgIdx.name: prtExPhPlDlciCnfgIdx
prtExPhPlDlciCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtExPhPlDlciSltIdx.name: prtExPhPlDlciSltIdx
prtExPhPlDlciSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid

prtExPhPlDlciPrtIdx.name: prtExPhPlDlciPrtIdx
prtExPhPlDlciPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique internal port number. PH.1/E1 and PH.1/T1 cards have three internal ports. Stand-alone units may have six such ports.

prtExPhPlDlciIdx.name: prtExPhPlDlciIdx
prtExPhPlDlciIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique index for each possible used dlci(16..991). When the protocol is not Multiplexing protocol, its type is 'user' and the only valid index is 1.

prtExPhPlDlciValid.name: prtExPhPlDlciValid
prtExPhPlDlciValid.description: This attribute indicates whether the attributes in this entry are valid or not. The user can add/delete pvc (dlci to dlci connection) by modifing this object

prtExPhPlDlciIConSlt.name: prtExPhPlDlciIConSlt
prtExPhPlDlciIConSlt.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position In the Mux (Agent) where the dlci is routed to. cl - will represent any of the CL slots. This value can be selected for multiple DLCIs of the product. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid

prtExPhPlDlciIConPrt.name: prtExPhPlDlciIConPrt
prtExPhPlDlciIConPrt.description: This attribute indicates a unique port id which the dlci is routed to. clNMS - will be used for NMS SNMP messages. It can be any port of the CL card. This value will be selectable only if prtExPhPlDlciIConSlt='cl' or 'notApplicable'.

prtExPhPlDlciIConDlci.name: prtExPhPlDlciIConDlci
prtExPhPlDlciIConDlci.description: This attribute indicates a unique internal connection dlci number, the dlci is routed to.

prtExPhPlDlciTxBc.name: prtExPhPlDlciTxBc
prtExPhPlDlciTxBc.description: This attribute indicates a unique Tx committed bandwidth on the user transmit line (or at the port receive line).

prtExPhPlDlciTxBe.name: prtExPhPlDlciTxBe
prtExPhPlDlciTxBe.description: This attribute indicates a unique Tx excess bandwidth on the user transmit line (or at the port receive line).

prtExPhPlDlciRxBc.name: prtExPhPlDlciRxBc
prtExPhPlDlciRxBc.description: This attribute indicates a unique Rx committed bandwidth on the user receive line (or at the port transmit line).

prtExPhPlDlciRxBe.name: prtExPhPlDlciRxBe
prtExPhPlDlciRxBe.description: This attribute indicates a unique Rx excess bandwidth on the user receive line (or at the port transmit line).

prtExPhPlDlciPriority.name: prtExPhPlDlciPriority
prtExPhPlDlciPriority.description: This attribute indicates a unique priority of the pcv. 1 is the lowest priority and 8 is the highest priority.

prtExPhPlDlciStatus.name: prtExPhPlDlciStatus
prtExPhPlDlciStatus.description: This attribute indicates the status of the pvc. The status is disconnected(1) when one of the sides is programmed as not connected

prtExPhPlModemTable.name: prtExPhPlModemTable
prtExPhPlModemTable.description: External Modem Parameters. The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only for the TmpCnfg entry.

prtExPhPlModemCnfgIdx.name: prtExPhPlModemCnfgIdx
prtExPhPlModemCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg.

prtExPhPlModemSltIdx.name: prtExPhPlModemSltIdx
prtExPhPlModemSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io12(16) are not valid

prtExPhPlModemPrtIdx.name: prtExPhPlModemPrtIdx
prtExPhPlModemPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port number. In case of PH.1 card, only exPrt(1) is valid.

prtExPhPlModemStatus.name: prtExPhPlModemStatus
prtExPhPlModemStatus.description: This object indicates whether a Dial Up Modem is enabled on this port. Default: disable

prtExPhPlModemActivate.name: prtExPhPlModemActivate
prtExPhPlModemActivate.description: This object indicates whether the Dial Up Modem is activated when the first frame is received or it is always activated. Default: onFirstFrame

prtExPhPlModemMaxIdleTime.name: prtExPhPlModemMaxIdleTime
prtExPhPlModemMaxIdleTime.description: Max Time allowed in Seconds without any traffic before the line is disconnected. Legal Values are: 1 sec, 2 sec .. 5 sec, 10 sec, 20 sec.. 1 min, 2 min .. 10 min, 15 min, 20 min, 25 min, 30 min. 65535 sec. means that this parameter is not applicable. Default: 1 sec.

prtExPhPlModemTimeBtwnCalls.name: prtExPhPlModemTimeBtwnCalls
prtExPhPlModemTimeBtwnCalls.description: Minimum Time in Seconds which is required after a call was disconnected. In this time no other call will be initiated from this Modem port even if there were frames transmitted to this port. This time is required for some Modems which have initializations that take a few seconds. Legal Values are: 0 sec. - 30 sec., 1-5 min. 65535 sec. means that this parameter is not applicable. Default: 0 sec

prtExPhPlModemCallDelay.name: prtExPhPlModemCallDelay
prtExPhPlModemCallDelay.description: Time in Seconds that the device will wait before dialing to the remote device. This feature is mostly used when there is a backup modem to the main link and the main link is down. In this case it is important to prevent the 2 devices from dialing through the backup modems to each other at the same time. It is advised to configure one side with a small call delay and the other side with a large call delay. Legal Values are: 0 - 30, 60, 120, 180, 240, 300, 600, 900, 1200, 1500, 1800 . 65535 sec. means that this parameter is not applicable. Default: 0 sec

prtExLs2CnfgTable.name: prtExLs2CnfgTable
prtExLs2CnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtExLs2CnfgIdx.name: prtExLs2CnfgIdx
prtExLs2CnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg

prtExLs2SltIdx.name: prtExLs2SltIdx
prtExLs2SltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid.

prtExLs2PrtIdx.name: prtExLs2PrtIdx
prtExLs2PrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique port index. For the Ls2/X.58 exPrt(7)..exPrt(10) are not valid.

prtExLs2Connect.name: prtExLs2Connect
prtExLs2Connect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms.

prtExLs2ClkMode.name: prtExLs2ClkMode
prtExLs2ClkMode.description: This attribute indicates a unique port operation clock mode.

prtExLs2EnvIdx.name: prtExLs2EnvIdx
prtExLs2EnvIdx.description: Envelope Index. When prtInLs2EnvAssign=auto, the value is 0 (not applicable).

prtInLs2CnfgTable.name: prtInLs2CnfgTable
prtInLs2CnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtInLs2CnfgIdx.name: prtInLs2CnfgIdx
prtInLs2CnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg

prtInLs2SltIdx.name: prtInLs2SltIdx
prtInLs2SltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid.

prtInLs2PrtIdx.name: prtInLs2PrtIdx
prtInLs2PrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique internal port index.

prtInLs2Connect.name: prtInLs2Connect
prtInLs2Connect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms. It also affects all the module considerations because the module has only one Internal interface which is the composite channel.

prtInLs2Group.name: prtInLs2Group
prtInLs2Group.description: This attribute indicates the group number of the port. LS-2 internal ports with the same group number share the same Time slot of the main link

prtInLs2Member.name: prtInLs2Member
prtInLs2Member.description: This attribute indicates the group member id of the port. This parameter is for the automatic envelope assignment algorithm.

prtInLs2LinkTo.name: prtInLs2LinkTo
prtInLs2LinkTo.description: It indicates the slot of the main link card to which the LS2 card is mapped. STATUS deprecated - this object is replaced by prtGenCnfgLinkToSlot and prtGenCnfgLinkToPort.

prtVc2CnfgTable.name: prtVc2CnfgTable
prtVc2CnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtVc2CnfgIdx.name: prtVc2CnfgIdx
prtVc2CnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relates to the TmpCnfg

prtVc2SltIdx.name: prtVc2SltIdx
prtVc2SltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. For Stand Alone products like WR: notApplicable (255)

prtVc2PrtIdx.name: prtVc2PrtIdx
prtVc2PrtIdx.description: A unique identifier of the port, within the card.

prtExVc2Connect.name: prtExVc2Connect
prtExVc2Connect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms.

prtExVc2TransGain.name: prtExVc2TransGain
prtExVc2TransGain.description: Transmit gain in dBm. For ports of VC-6A and VC-6AG cards, the units will be 0.1dBm because valid values can be in 0.5dBm steps.

prtExVc2ReceiveGain.name: prtExVc2ReceiveGain
prtExVc2ReceiveGain.description: Receive gain in dBm. For ports of VC-6A and VC-6AG cards, the units will be 0.1dBm because valid values can be in 0.5dBm steps.

prtExVc2Wire.name: prtExVc2Wire
prtExVc2Wire.description: This object is equal for all the ports in the specific card because of HW limitations. For FXO & FXS this parameter is not applicable.

prtExVc2CodingLaw.name: prtExVc2CodingLaw
prtExVc2CodingLaw.description: This attribute indicates the Method/Law for decoding/encoding the voice information. aLaw(1) is the standard Law for E1 links. uLaw(2) is the standard Law for T1 links. This object is equal for all the ports in the specific module because of HW limitations

prtExVc2Sig.name: prtExVc2Sig
prtExVc2Sig.description: This attribute indicates the method for decoding/encoding the signaling information(on/off hook). noSignaling (1) - not using signaling (only voice). robbedBitMultiFrame(2) - is the standard method for T1 links and proprietary method for E1 links. chAssociatedE1 (3) - is valid only for E1 G.732S links. robbedBitFrame (4) - is proprietary method implimenting 7 bit for the voice and 1 bit dedicated for signaling. This object is equal for all the ports in the specific module because of HW limitations.

prtExVc2Oos.name: prtExVc2Oos
prtExVc2Oos.description: This object is equal for all the ports in the specific card because of HW limitations

prtExVc2LinkTo.name: prtExVc2LinkTo
prtExVc2LinkTo.description: This attribute indicates the slot of the ML card to which the VC card is mapped. STATUS deprecated - this object is replaced by prtGenCnfgLinkToSlot and prtGenCnfgLinkToPort.

prtExVc2OperMode.name: prtExVc2OperMode
prtExVc2OperMode.description: This object indicates the operation mode of the port. normal = bi-directional (Tx/Rx) unidirectRx = unidirectional Rx. broadcast = Tx upon request.

prtExVc2SigProfile.name: prtExVc2SigProfile
prtExVc2SigProfile.description: This object indicates the Signaling Profile of the port. notApplicable - for VC-2 family and when prtExVc2Sig=noSignaling(1) p1 = profile 1 p2 = profile 2 p3 = profile 3 p4 = profile 4

prtExVc2CallEnable.name: prtExVc2CallEnable
prtExVc2CallEnable.description: This object indicates the Enabled Call direction. notApplicable - for all cards except VC-2/R2. both - incoming + outgoing.

prtExVc2R2Delay.name: prtExVc2R2Delay
prtExVc2R2Delay.description: This object indicates the R2 Delay. notApplicable - for all cards except VC-2/R2.

prtExVc2CasStd.name: prtExVc2CasStd
prtExVc2CasStd.description: This object indicates the CAS (Channel Associated Signaling) Standard. notApplicable - for all cards except VC-2/R2.

prtExVc2EchoCanceler.name: prtExVc2EchoCanceler
prtExVc2EchoCanceler.description: Echo canceler activation. notApplicable - for VC-2 and VC-6 cards.

prtExVc2TxBitCode.name: prtExVc2TxBitCode
prtExVc2TxBitCode.description: - - - For MP & FCD - - - This object represents 4 parameters, by 2 Octets : Tx D Bit Code-MSB nibble, Tx C Bit Code- nibble, Tx B Bit Code- nibble, Tx A Bit Code-LSB nibble. Each nibble: 0 hex = 0000 = Not Applicable 1 hex = 0001 = M lead 2 hex = 0010 = M lead inverse 3 hex = 0011 = Reverse Polarity 4 hex = 0100 = Metering Pulse 5 hex = 0101 = Forced 1 6 hex = 0110 = Forced 0 7-F hex - not used (invalid values) This object will be RO if prtExVc2SigProfile is NOT manual. - - - For WR II - - - This object represents the following 4 parameters by 2 Octets: 1. On/Off hook signaling transmission mode from the FXS towards the T1/E1 (MSB nibble 1). 2. Default signaling bits that are not in use (nibble 2). 3. Ring Detection signaling transmission mode from the FXO towards the T1/E1(nibble 3). 4. M (Mouth) Signaling transmission mode from the E&M towards the T1/E1(LSB nibble 4). Each nibble: --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Value On/Off Hook Default sig. Ring Detect. M (Mouth) --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 0 hex = 0000 Not Applicable Not Applicable. Not Applicable Not Applicable 1 hex = 0001 Tx A bit Values 1-3 are Tx A bit Tx A bit 2 hex = 0010 Tx A bit inverse for On/Off Hook Tx A bit inv. Tx A bit inv. 3 hex = 0011 Tx B bit A,B,A Inv,B Inv. Tx B bit Tx B bit 4 hex = 0100 Tx B bit inverse Values 4-7 are Tx B bit inv. Tx B bit inv. 5 hex = 0101 not Used-invalid for On/Off Hook not Used-invalid not Used-invalid 6 hex = 0110 not Used-invalid A, A Inverse. not Used-invalid not Used-invalid 7 hex = 0111 not Used-invalid not Used-invalid not Used-invalid 8 hex = 1000 not Used-invalid Values 8-11 are not Used-invalid not Used-invalid 9 hex = 1001 not Used-invalid for On/Off Hook not Used-invalid not Used-invalid A hex = 1010 not used-invalid B, B Inverse. not Used-invalid not Used-invalid B hex = 1011 not used-invalid The Bits order: not Used-invalid not Used-invalid C-F hex not used-invalid ABCD not Used-invalid not Used-invalid Default value: 11 11

prtExVc2RxBitOutput.name: prtExVc2RxBitOutput
prtExVc2RxBitOutput.description: - - - For MP & FCD - - - This object represents 3 parameters by 2 Octets: Spare -MSB nibble, always=0 hex E Lead Output - nibble, Reverse Polarity Output- nibble, Metering Pulse Output -LSB nibble. Each nibble: 0 hex = 0000 = Not Applicable 1 hex = 0001 = Rx A bit 2 hex = 0010 = Rx A bit inverse 3 hex = 0011 = Rx B bit 4 hex = 0100 = Rx B bit inverse 5 hex = 0101 = Rx C bit 6 hex = 0110 = Rx C bit inverse 7 hex = 0111 = Rx D bit 8 hex = 1000 = Rx D bit inverse 9 hex = 1001 = none A-F hex - not used (invalid values) This object will be RO if prtExVc2SigProfile is NOT manual. - - - For WR II - - - This object represents the following 2 parameters in 1 Octet: 1. On/Off hook signaling receive mode from the T1/E1 into the FXS/FXO (MSB nibble 1). 2. E (Ear) Signaling receive mode from the T1/E1 into the E&M (LSB nibble 2). Each nibble: --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Value On/Off Hook E (Ear) --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 0 hex = 0000 Not Applicable Not Applicable 1 hex = 0001 Rx A bit Rx A bit 2 hex = 0010 Rx A bit inverse Rx A bit inverse 3 hex = 0011 Rx B bit Rx B bit 4 hex = 0100 Rx B bit inverse Rx B bit inverse 5-F hex not used-invalid not Used-invalid Default value: 11

prtExVc2MeterRate.name: prtExVc2MeterRate
prtExVc2MeterRate.description: This entry is applicable only for VC-6A/FXO and VC-6A/FXS. Meter Rate means rate of Call Meter in Public Phones, in KHz units. Must be the same for all card's ports.

prtExVc2IfSignaling.name: prtExVc2IfSignaling
prtExVc2IfSignaling.description: This entry is applicable only for VC-6A and VC-6AG cards. Interface Analog Signaling. Must be the same for all card's ports. loopStart - for the usual trunk/phone types. groundStart - for trunks that need Ground signaling (applicable for VC-6AG cards.

prtExVc2SeizeAck.name: prtExVc2SeizeAck
prtExVc2SeizeAck.description: This parameter shows whether the device will acknowledge a seize signal (On/Off Hook). When the value is set to yes(3) & the device receives an on/off hook signal it will transmit back an on/off hook signal. When the value is set to no(2) & the device receives an on/off hook signal it will NOT transmit back an on/off hook signal. Default value for WR FXO: no(2).

prtExVc2EandMType.name: prtExVc2EandMType
prtExVc2EandMType.description: This is the signaling type on the E&M analog side. The analog signaling includes voltage, no. of pins and other parameters.

prtHsfCnfgTable.name: prtHsfCnfgTable
prtHsfCnfgTable.description: The write operation into the Table Objects is valid only to the TmpCnfg entry.

prtHsfCnfgIdx.name: prtHsfCnfgIdx
prtHsfCnfgIdx.description: This attribute indicates the Idx of the Cnfg (1..100) being accessed. Idx 255 relate to the TmpCnfg.

prtHsfSltIdx.name: prtHsfSltIdx
prtHsfSltIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique slot position where the card is inserted. In the ?004 Unit the entries io6(10)..io16) are not valid.

prtHsfPrtIdx.name: prtHsfPrtIdx
prtHsfPrtIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique external port index. Hs2 has only two ports (exPrt1,exPrt2). Hs3 has three ports (exPrt1,exPrt2,exPrt3). Hsq and hsqN has four ports. Hs6 has six external ports. Hs12 has twelve external ports.

prtExHsfConnect.name: prtExHsfConnect
prtExHsfConnect.description: This attribute indicates whether the port should be considered in any of the mux algorithms.

prtExHsfRate.name: prtExHsfRate
prtExHsfRate.description: This attribute indicates the port speed.

prtExHsfClkMode.name: prtExHsfClkMode
prtExHsfClkMode.description: This attribute indicates a unique port operation clock mode.

prtExHsfCts.name: prtExHsfCts

prtExHs4LineLen.name: prtExHs4LineLen

prtExHs4TsIdx.name: prtExHs4TsIdx
prtExHs4TsIdx.description: This attribute indicates a unique time slot position. The valid time slots are: 1..24 for T1 Card and 1..31 for E1 interface. In G732S-E1 lines, time slot 16 is not valid for data, it is dedicated to multiframe synchronization bits and voice signaling.

For HS-S , only 'te' and 'nt' are applicable. For HS-U, this object is not applicable. For HS-U6, HS-U12, are applicable: 'lt'=lt-i,'nt'=nt-i, lt1.

prtExHsiActType.name: prtExHsiActType
prtExHsiActType.description: It indicates the Activation Type. Activation Type is the Synchronization type towards the PBX. It is applicable only when prtExHsiInterface=nt. notApplicable - for cards that do not support this object, or when prtExHsiInterface is NOT nt.
